qx|o5|st||md|4S2TJH25D678TQKCKA,S58KH34KD29AC468Q,S49QAH678JD45C35T,|rh||ah|Board 6|sv|e|mb|p|mb|1D|mb|d|mb|p|mb|1H|mb|p|mb|p|mb|d|mb|p|mb|2D|mb|p|mb|p|mb|p|nt|lioncub: 1@D opener. I want you all to remember this hand for the rest of your lives  A double would show 12+ points with shortage in diamonds and GUARANTEEING 4-CARD SUPPORT IN SPADES AND HEARTS WITH TOLERANCE FOR CLUBS. THIS HAND HAS NEITHER and is the 4/3/3/3 hand with under 16 points. With 16 points you can just about bid 1NT. With this hand honestly peoples there is just one bid to make and that is PASS. The rest of bidding ain't so good either. The 1@H response by East would show under 7 points. The bid is 2@H showing 7 to 9 and certainly should bid again over the double by North. But North why double?  West has shown hearts and spades BELIEVE HIM. Just pass. The double by North of course is take out and not penalty. I would bid: 1@D-p-1@H-p;  2@D-p-p-p. A take out double should ideally be 4/4/4/1 with opening hand. Over a minor guarantees both majors. Over a major guarantees 4-cards in other major. lioncub: Lead & claim.|
