qx|o10|st||md|1S678TAH9D23TJC35T,S9H57TAD579KC479Q,S45H468JQD68AC26A,|rh||ah|Board 11|sv|o|mb|p|mb|p|mb|1H|mb|1S|mb|p|mb|1N|mb|p|mb|2N|mb|p|mb|p|mb|p|nt|Opening bid........does not satisfy rule of 20.  However, at third place you can stretch it a bit.  1@S is sound overcall. Pass by South is okay. Does West like her partner's overcall? The answer is NO. 1NT in West MUST show min of 11 points or a very good ten. Don't forget your partner has not opened......just made an overcall. There is one bid left for West to make ... PASS. On the other hand, East over 1NT should trust West and bid 3NT. An overcall shows a good suit..........not points. Again we are bringing up the topic of disciplined bidding and being able to trust partner to have his bid. The recommended bids are:P-1@H-1@S; P, P, P. Someone just asked whether E should have bid 1NT with 15 points. The answer is no.....always show 5-card major. 
